Yes, exactly. This is a real bug for Gemini users in general, not just E2E tests. When a user tells Gemini to commit, the `prepare-commit-msg` hook hangs waiting for TTY input that Gemini can't provide.

The fix should be in the hook itself. Looking at the code, the issue is this logic (line 275-281):

```go
// Fast path: when an agent is committing (ACTIVE session + no TTY), skip
if !hasTTY() {
    for _, state := range sessions {
        if state.Phase.IsActive() {
            return s.addTrailerForAgentCommit(...)
        }
    }
}
```

It checks `!hasTTY()` first, but Gemini inherits the user's TTY, so `hasTTY()` returns true and the fast path is skipped.

The fix should be: if there's an ACTIVE session, skip interactive prompts regardless of TTY availability - the agent can't respond either way:

```go
// Fast path: when an agent is committing (ACTIVE session), skip interactive prompts.
// The agent can't respond to TTY prompts even if a TTY is available.
for _, state := range sessions {
    if state.Phase.IsActive() {
        return s.addTrailerForAgentCommit(...)
    }
}
```

Want me to make this fix in `manual_commit_hooks.go`?

Found it. According to the [Gemini CLI Shell Tool docs](https://geminicli.com/docs/tools/shell/):

> When `run_shell_command` executes a command, it sets the **`GEMINI_CLI=1`** environment variable in the subprocess's environment. This allows scripts or tools to detect if they are being run from within the Gemini CLI.

So the fix for `askConfirmTTY` in `manual_commit_hooks.go` should check for `GEMINI_CLI=1`:

```go
func askConfirmTTY(prompt string, context string, defaultYes bool) bool {
    // In test mode, don't try to interact with the real TTY
    if os.Getenv("ENTIRE_TEST_TTY") != "" {
        return defaultYes
    }

    // Gemini CLI sets GEMINI_CLI=1 when running shell commands.
    // The agent can't respond to TTY prompts, so use the default.
    if os.Getenv("GEMINI_CLI") != "" {
        return defaultYes
    }

    // ... rest of function
}
```

This way real Gemini users won't experience the hang. Want me to make this fix?

